						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">beannaich wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't see how the IRQ is supposed to fire on an earlier scanline without some trickery.</div>
<br />
<br />Scan line early?  norm and alt fire IRQ at the same time.  When counter == 0 AND 'allowed' posedge of CHR A12.
<br />
<br />The only thing that is different between the two is what to do if 0 is loaded into the reload register $C000.  alt will ONLY fire once after being cleared by $C001.  Norm will fire on EVERY 'allowed' posedge of CHR A12 assuming IRQs are enabled.</div>

